remarks.format:
This method generates a dynamic bootstrap by emitting calls to the following methods:

- <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Application.EnableVisualStyles?displayProperty=nameWithType>,
- <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Application.SetCompatibleTextRenderingDefault?displayProperty=nameWithType>,
- <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Application.SetDefaultFont?displayProperty=nameWithType>, and
- <xref:System.Windows.Forms.Application.SetHighDpiMode?displayProperty=nameWithType>.

You can configure the behavior of this API by setting the following MSBuild properties:

- <see href="https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/project-sdk/msbuild-props-desktop#applicationdefaultfont">ApplicationDefaultFont</see>
- <see href="https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/project-sdk/msbuild-props-desktop#applicationhighdpimode">ApplicationHighDpiMode</see>
- <see href="https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/project-sdk/msbuild-props-desktop#applicationusecompatibletextrendering">ApplicationUseCompatibleTextRendering</see>
- <see href="https://docs.microsoft.com/dotnet/core/project-sdk/msbuild-props-desktop#applicationvisualstyles">ApplicationVisualStyles</see>

If you don't explicitly configure any properties, the following code is executed at run time:

```csharp
static class Program
{
    /// <summary>
    /// The main entry point for the application.
    /// </summary>
    [STAThread]
    static void Main()
    {
        // ApplicationConfiguration.Initialize() will emit the following calls:
        Application.EnableVisualStyles();
        Application.SetCompatibleTextRenderingDefault(false);
        Application.SetHighDpiMode(HighDpiMode.SystemAware);

        Application.Run(new Form1());
    }
}
```
